                  <Abstract ID="Abs1" Language="En">
                     <Heading>Abstract</Heading>
                     <Para>Introducing a variable cosmological function Λ(<Emphasis Type="Italic">t</Emphasis>) in a geometrical manner from a 5D Riemann-flat metric, we investigate the possibility of having a geometric criterion to choose a suitable cosmological function Λ(<Emphasis Type="Italic">t</Emphasis>) for every 4D dynamical hypersurface capable of generating phantom cosmologies.</Para>
                  </Abstract>
